Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.44,0:02:15.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In the beginning of the Paleozoic Era, the Cambrian explosion occurred,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.68,0:02:17.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and a large number of organisms made their appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.82,0:02:19.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Then, at the end of the Paleozoic Era,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.16,0:02:21.06,Dialogue,,0,0,28,,{\i1}the world changes to \Nan infinite spread of 2 tatami,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.80,0:02:20.97,Tatami Age,,0,0,0,,{\fad(170,190)\blur0.6\c&H799C85&\t(0,170,\c&HFCFCFC&)\t(980,1170,\c&H799C85&)}2-Tatami Age \N(Permian Period)
Dialogue: 1,0:02:19.80,0:02:20.97,Tatami Age,,0,0,0,,{\fad(170,190)\bord0\be1\c&H799C85&\t(0,170,\c&HFCFCFC&)\t(980,1170,\c&H799C85&)}2-Tatami Age \N(Permian Period)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.06,0:02:24.78,Dialogue,,120,120,0,,{\i1}and in the beginning of the Mesozoic Era, \Nit increases by one as the "3-Tatami Age" arrives.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.30,0:02:24.47,Tatami Age,,0,0,0,,{\fad(170,190)\blur0.6\c&H85A7AD&\t(0,170,\c&HFCFCFC&)\t(980,1170,\c&H85A7AD&)}3-Tatami Age
Dialogue: 1,0:02:23.30,0:02:24.47,Tatami Age,,0,0,0,,{\fad(170,190)\bord0\be1\c&H85A7AD&\t(0,170,\c&HFCFCFC&)\t(980,1170,\c&H85A7AD&)}3-Tatami Age
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.78,0:02:26.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But as the dinosaurs appeared,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.88,0:02:29.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the laid-out tatami were \Ncompletely stomped into nothingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.11,0:02:31.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and time moved on to the Jurassic Period.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.81,0:02:30.98,Tatami Age,,0,0,0,,{\fad(170,190)\blur0.6\c&HA09992&\t(0,170,\c&HFCFCFC&)\t(980,1170,\c&HA09992&)}Jurassic Period
Dialogue: 1,0:02:29.81,0:02:30.98,Tatami Age,,0,0,0,,{\fad(170,190)\bord0\be1\c&HA09992&\t(0,170,\c&HFCFCFC&)\t(980,1170,\c&HA09992&)}Jurassic Period
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.56,0:02:32.73,Tatami Age,,0,0,0,,{\fad(170,190)\blur0.6\c&HA8ABAB&\t(0,170,\c&HFCFCFC&)\t(980,1170,\c&HA8ABAB&)}Cretaceous Period
Dialogue: 1,0:02:31.56,0:02:32.73,Tatami Age,,0,0,0,,{\fad(170,190)\bord0\be1\c&HA8ABAB&\t(0,170,\c&HFCFCFC&)\t(980,1170,\c&HA8ABAB&)}Cretaceous Period
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.52,0:02:34.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}After that came the \Nmajestic glory of humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.02,0:02:34.19,Tatami Age,,0,0,0,,{\fad(170,190)\blur0.6\c&HA8ABAB&\t(0,170,\c&HFCFCFC&)\t(980,1170,\c&HA8ABAB&)}Tertiary Period
Dialogue: 1,0:02:33.02,0:02:34.19,Tatami Age,,0,0,0,,{\fad(170,190)\bord0\be1\c&HA8ABAB&\t(0,170,\c&HFCFCFC&)\t(980,1170,\c&HA8ABAB&)}Tertiary Period
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.36,0:02:35.25,Dialogue,,120,120,0,,{\i1}And before long, in the present world,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:35.04,0:02:36.24,Tatami Age,,0,0,0,,{\fad(170,190)\bord0\be1\c&HA8ABAB&\t(0,170,\c&HFCFCFC&)\t(980,1170,\c&HA8ABAB&)}Quaternary Period
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.25,0:02:37.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}as the bell tolls for the end of the \Nquaternary part of the Cenozoic Era,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.13,0:02:38.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}once again, tatami have been spread out across the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.77,0:02:40.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}marking the beginning \Nof the "4.5-Tatami Age."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.80,0:02:41.51,Tatami Age,,0,0,0,,{\fad(170,0)\blur0.6\c&HA8ABAB&\t(0,170,\c&HFCFCFC&)\t(760,1710,\c&H090B0B&)}4.5-Tatami Age
Dialogue: 1,0:02:39.80,0:02:41.51,Tatami Age,,0,0,0,,{\fad(170,0)\bord0\be1\c&HA8ABAB&\t(0,170,\c&HFCFCFC&)\t(760,1710,\c&H090B0B&)}4.5-Tatami Age
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.27,0:02:45.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Going back in time is quite unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.64,0:02:47.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}However, I was wandering,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.52,0:02:51.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}lost in an unbelievable world of infinitely many 4.5-tatami rooms laid side by side.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.01,0:02:53.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It had already been two months since I began wandering.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.83,0:02:55.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Even though I figured this world had no end,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.63,0:02:58.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I continued my pitiful, endless march.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.53,0:03:01.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"If I open the door, there is the hallway."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.08,0:03:04.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That would be an astronomical, \Nmiraculous, and fortuitous happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.22,0:03:06.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}All the rooms look the same, \Nbut they all have slight differences.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.91,0:03:09.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Each one was inhabited \Nby a slightly different me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.88,0:03:13.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}However, all of them seemed to have led \Nsome gloriously wasted campus life.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.54,0:03:18.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I tried to begin studying each one \Nand myself as a whole,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.64,0:03:19.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but I immediately lost my motivation,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.90,0:03:24.86,Dialogue,,120,120,0,,{\i1}and instead, my interest shifted to the traces in \Neach room of the various people I was surrounded by.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.90,0:03:28.61,Dialogue,,40,40,0,,{\i1}The person named Aijima was one year older than me \Nand the head of the Library Committee.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.61,0:03:31.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He was a small man who would not allow you to check out more than two books at once,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.00,0:03:32.90,Dialogue,,120,120,0,,{\i1}but you could see in his eyes through those glasses \Nthat his polite face masked hypocrisy,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.90,0:03:34.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and I got an impression he was insufferable.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.76,0:03:39.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I recall seeing something of a purge in \Nsome secret society that he was in charge of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.14,0:03:40.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}after someone entrapped him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.57,0:03:44.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Now that I think about it, earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.96,0:03:50.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know a Higuchi who lives on the second floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.03,0:03:51.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.20,0:03:52.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.75,0:03:55.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We are collecting information on this man.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.03,0:03:59.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This guy has caused everyone \Nquite a lot of trouble, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.16,0:04:02.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's like some youkai with \Nno redeemable qualities at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.94,0:04:05.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The two that came calling had their faces covered,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.02,0:04:08.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but that vocal tick had to have been Aijima.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.13,0:04:11.54,Dialogue,,120,120,0,,Then I'm going to tell you a number of things. \NIf anything comes to mind, answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.06,0:04:13.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Airship.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.35,0:04:14.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gozan.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.36,0:04:15.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Honwaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.71,0:04:16.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kohinata.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.66,0:04:22.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Kohinata-san is the poster child of a raven-haired maiden on campus.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.05,0:04:24.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If I were ever perchance to meet her,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.07,0:04:27.83,Dialogue,,120,120,0,,{\i1}I bet I would lavish her with gifts without a second thought, regardless of the hardship on myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.79,0:04:32.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}With their word association game not bearing any fruit, the two left.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.29,0:04:36.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That dental hygienist Hanuki-san \Nwas also an alumni of my university.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.81,0:04:39.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And I knew that the two of them \Nwere in the same year.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.75,0:04:42.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}While I'm mentioning it, that cart owner also seems to be from the same year.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.51,0:04:43.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's a small world, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.01,0:04:47.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mr. Higuchi is an eighth-year student \Non the brink of failure,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.09,0:04:50.02,Dialogue,,120,120,0,,{\i1}but he's fixed in his ways and takes things at \Nhis own pace, although he has a stately manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.88,0:04:53.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hanuki-san would frequently \Nvisit him at the boarding house,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.27,0:04:55.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and it seems like he took on \Na couple of apprentices.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.85,0:04:57.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Why was he so revered?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.49,0:05:00.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}His extremely useless life and \Nhis propensity for fierce self-effacement...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.16,0:05:02.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Perhaps it was all lined with deep learning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.55,0:05:07.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In one of my lives, I had become his disciple.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.16,0:05:10.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The man whose entire body seemed chiseled out of stone, Mr. Jougasaki,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.33,0:05:14.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}seemed to have taken over some war of pranks with Mr. Higuchi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.66,0:05:11.66,Glue,,0,0,0,,{\pos(112.902,61.561)\p1\blur1.5\c&HDADFF2&}m 964.625 169.375 l 950.625 206 967.375 226 1156.625 230 1172.625 191.375 1158 173.375 1059.375 169.375
Dialogue: 1,0:05:10.66,0:05:11.66,Glue,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1065.553,238.885)\be1}Glue
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.05,0:05:15.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He doesn't look like that sort of person at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.71,0:05:18.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but he succeeded as \Nthe next proxy or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.77,0:05:24.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}While Mr. Jougasaki had \Na lover named Kaori-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.02,0:05:25.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}he seemed to have some interest in Hanuki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.64,0:05:28.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hanuki-san seemed to both be \Ndating Mr. Higuchi and not dating him,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.88,0:05:31.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and anyway Mr. Higuchi said that \Nhe was going on a trip around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.85,0:05:33.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will you come with me, Hanuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.64,0:05:36.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can speak English, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.18,0:05:38.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be crazy. This is foolish.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.64,0:05:42.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mr. Higuchi has feelings for Hanuki-san, and yet he's going to leave her...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.11,0:05:43.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}How frustrating.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.04,0:05:46.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Perhaps it's like he's pretending not to notice the diamond dropped on the roadside?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.29,0:05:51.62,Dialogue,,120,120,0,,{\i1}Looking at it like this, humans really are deep. \NThey have many faces.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.62,0:05:55.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's a huge shame to scorn people just because of a single hasty look on the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.36,0:05:58.13,Dialogue,,120,120,0,,{\i1}If you look at them from all angles, \Nyou'll be able to see new, hidden sides to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.68,0:06:01.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I will put everything that I've been up in this shelf,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.23,0:06:03.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and once having put them aside, \NI won't dare to take them down again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.93,0:06:06.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}However, I should have been \Nsatisfied to the point of bursting
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.63,0:06:09.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}by all these different people \Nsurrounding my campus lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.15,0:06:10.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What in the world was I doing?
Dialogue: 3,0:06:10.81,0:06:13.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I knew not how to partake of the world.
